## Conjecture (CPRR)
- Hypothesis: Alpine splits Guile's optional bindings into
  separate apk packages to keep the base image small. readline,
  curses, and bytestructures are all separate. Distros that ship
  monolithic packages (FreeBSD ports, Homebrew, Debian) include
  readline by default which is why the bug only surfaced in CI.

## Validation
- Searching apk for the readline binding:
  apk info guile-readline → \"Guile readline support\"
- Build error stack trace explicitly named (ice-9 readline) as
  the missing module — direct evidence.

## Refutation / known limits
- We don't pin the package version (no =3.0.x suffix), so an
  Alpine package upgrade could break the build later. Acceptable
  for now; can pin in a follow-up if Alpine ships a guile-readline
  with an ABI break.
- We don't audit the runtime image for OTHER missing optional
  bindings (curses, threads, etc). If sage starts using more
  ice-9 modules, we may hit the same class of error again.
- Build matrix only covers amd64. ARM64 image would need its own
  validation; out of scope.

